#Deploying Jenkins App on Azure
1.Open Azure portal using the link (https://portal.azure.com/?azure-
portal=true%5D#home)​  
*2.Create a Resource Group in Azure portal.​  
 -Create an VM in the respective resource group.​  
 -Provide a name for your VM.​  
 -Select your image as UBUNTU​.  
 -Select SSH public key and generate the keypair.​  
 -Once VM is created you can see all the attributes related to the VM like
subnets,vnets,etc.,​  
*3.SSH into VM using VM public ip address using gitbash or any terminal.​  
  -First, change the permissions of the pem file using command: chmod 600
Jenkins_key.pem.​  
  -SSH into azure VM using "ssh -I jenkins_key.pem azureuser@vmpublicipaddress".​  
